<paragraph pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Description of the subgenus.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Annuals; bracteoles present; pedicels conspicuous (1.35-3.0 mm long); flowers single or clustered (2-6 per node); stigmas 3-5, thin. The species are mostly distributed in Brazil, with irradiations to the neighbouring countries.</paragraph>
